Search strategy

A systematic review will be conducted in accordance with the Preferred Reporting Items for Systematic Reviews and Meta-Analyses (PRISMA) guidelines (Moher et al., 2009). The following databases will be searched using the keywords alcohol consumption, drinking behaviour, mood, emotions, affective states: PsycINFO, PsycARTICLES, Science Direct, Wiley Online Library, SCOPUS, PubMed, Web of Science, JSTOR. Additional articles will be located by reading the references of the retrieved articles. To gain a full understanding of the literature and control for unpublished non-significant findings, grey literature will be included in the review as well. This will be obtained by emailing research group leaders of labs conducting this kind of work.

Inclusion and exclusion criteria

The inclusion criteria are as follows: 
•	peer-reviewed papers;
•	grey literature;
•	focus on the general human population (non-clinical sample);
•	looking at AS on the day prior to consumption;
•	papers in English or Russian.

Exclusion criteria:
•	reviews and editorials;
•	literature examining mood disorders;
•	literature examining AUDs.

